<section class="detail">
  <h1>About Université de Valmoure</h1>

  <p>
    Founded in 1887, Université de Valmoure is a public research university located in Valmoure, France.
    With over 28,000 students across three campuses, the university offers a wide range of undergraduate,
    graduate and doctoral programs in sciences, engineering, humanities and social sciences.
  </p>

  <p>
    Our mission is to provide high-quality education, foster groundbreaking research, and maintain strong
    ties with industry and international partners. Every year, the university publishes hundreds of
    opportunities for students and researchers: academic programs, courses, research positions,
    internships, events and thesis subjects.
  </p>

  <h2>Campuses</h2>
  <ul>
    <li>Campus Nord — Engineering and Computer Science</li>
    <li>Campus Sud — Sciences and Mathematics</li>
    <li>Campus Centre — Humanities, Law and Social Sciences</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>Contact</h2>
